<subSubSection id="A779936F6ED8F905BA406658DEB0992A" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph id="2DA4DA05382492B5A6A6A9953E074B67" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58696CF5A6079A210F8AFCCCFE23B216" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. Records of 
<taxonomicName id="9EF90B2B44A4AFDD3BB06EF9FB99FAE6" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphaerosyllis brevicirra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevicirra">Sphaerosyllis brevicirra</taxonomicName>
from the Western Mediterranean by 
<bibRefCitation id="A93C7A1319DB4F83B845BCB32A49C9F2" author="Alos, C" journalOrPublisher="Cahiers de Biologie Marine" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="329 - 339" title="Adiciones a la fauna de anelidos poliquetos de la peninsula Iberica: familia Syllidae" volume="30" year="1989">
<normalizedToken id="D948E522BCE01E7C02EE15E7660001D5" originalValue="Alós">Alos</normalizedToken>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
and from the Aegean Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="28250DFD41B9E9A210F40A805491A40E" author="Simboura, Nomiki" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. National and Kapodistrian University of Athens, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Θαλάσσοι μακροβενθικοί Πολύxαιτοι (AnnelidaPolychaeta) της Ελλάδας: Συστηματική, Οικολογία, Ζωογεωγραφία" year="1996">Simboura 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="D95CA54C509A5400B0635ED14C5A5599" author="Cinar, Melih Ertan" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Ege University, Izmir" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Tuerkiye'nin Ege Denizi sahillerinde dagilim goesteren Syllidae (Polychaeta-Annelida) tuerlerinin taksonomisi ve ekolojisi" year="1999">
<normalizedToken id="0D0F09E7B980554A18268E24A227570D" originalValue="Çınar">Cinar</normalizedToken>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
) belong to an undescribed 
<taxonomicName id="DB6CEE064F38E12F04DB10BE0A5EFE84" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Prosphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosphaerosyllis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Prosphaerosyllis</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation id="C289E27A858BA174BD42BF91DC016C43" author="San Martin, G." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Iberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 544 pp" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos MA, et al. (Eds)" volume="21, Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" year="2003">
San 
<normalizedToken id="2AC113314EE12350A45BC4583DF7EFCF" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="58C3D496483A859BD0A4002411599EB3" author="Faulwetter, Sarah" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="281 - 326" title="An account of the taxonomy and distribution of Syllidae (Annelida, Polychaetes) in the eastern Mediterranean, with notes on the genus Prosphaerosyllis San Martin, 1984 in the Mediterranean" volume="150" year="2011">Faulwetter et al. (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
examined the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="D0596A8D9779FCAE6932D690B792FC23" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Prosphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevicirra">Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra</taxonomicName>
from the Red Sea and found that the species bears a conspicuous papilla on each dorsal cirrus. All descriptions and illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="CA1DB36F5529627AB3812A012C0BF005" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Prosphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevicirra">Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra</taxonomicName>
from the Mediterranean lack these papillae. In addition, these specimen descriptions differ from 
<taxonomicName id="1324E0B21DF07C09269AB12B1A860B98" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Prosphaerosyllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevicirra">Prosphaerosyllis brevicirra</taxonomicName>
by the absence of dorsal cirri on chaetiger 2 (reported as present by 
<bibRefCitation id="05C8C1077BF794382C29E21C7DA8EB10" author="Alos, C" journalOrPublisher="Cahiers de Biologie Marine" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="329 - 339" title="Adiciones a la fauna de anelidos poliquetos de la peninsula Iberica: familia Syllidae" volume="30" year="1989">
<normalizedToken id="F0618CD89FB572B6B73AED9711F6D3F2" originalValue="Alós">Alos</normalizedToken>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
but in fact absent (
<bibRefCitation id="506215E08F861FA93F24F0DA8D7F50B4" author="San Martin, G." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Iberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 544 pp" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos MA, et al. (Eds)" volume="21, Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" year="2003">
San 
<normalizedToken id="EC69A907AB5B9F32222D9609AA15EC2C" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
) and by thicker aciculae.
</paragraph>
